AMR Corp's American Airlines andCitibank are expected to announce a joint marketing program ata press conference tomorrow, analysts said.    The program will probably allow consumers using a creditcard issued by Citibank to pay for flights on American and earnfrequent flyer miles, they said.    "It's an incentive to use the card and it potentiallybuilds traffic for the carrier," said one analyst, who askednot to be named.    One analyst noted that Texas Air Corp's &lt;TEX> ContinentalAirlines has a similar agreement with a bank issuingMastercard.    Texas Air officials were not immediately available.    American Airlines and Citibank scheduled a press conferenceat 1030 EST in New York tomorrow to announce a "major newcredit card alliance marketing program."    Spokesmen for Citibank declined additional comment.American Airlines spokesmen were not available. Reuter&#3;